## 🚌 Medical Transportation (NEMT)

> Tools for building Non-Emergency Medical Transportation systems that serve Medicaid patients in the US.

*NEMT is a required Medicaid benefit. 3.6 million Americans miss medical appointments each year due to transportation. It's a $5B+ US market.*

### Routing & Dispatch (Open Source)

- **[OpenRouteService](https://openrouteservice.org/)** — Free routing API. Supports wheelchair-accessible routes, multi-stop optimization, and travel time matrices. Can be self-hosted. Free API key available.
  > *Use this as the routing backbone for an NEMT dispatch system. Free alternative to Google Maps API.*

- **[Vroom](https://github.com/VROOM-Project/vroom)** — Free, open-source vehicle route optimization engine. Solves the core NEMT problem: which driver picks up which patient in what order to minimize cost and time. MIT license.

- **[OSRM (Open Source Routing Machine)](http://project-osrm.org/)** — Very fast, free routing engine. Can process millions of routes per day. Self-hostable. Used as a backend by major routing companies.

- **[GraphHopper](https://www.graphhopper.com/)** — Open-source routing engine with a free tier API. Supports vehicle routing, isochrones, and map matching. Java-based.

- **[OpenTripPlanner](https://www.opentripplanner.org/)** — Open-source multimodal trip planner. Combines public transit (via GTFS) + walking + driving. Good for building transit-aware NEMT alternatives.

### US-Specific NEMT Data & Standards

- **[CMS NEMT Open Data](https://data.cms.gov/)** — Free data from the Centers for Medicare & Medicaid Services. Includes Medicaid transportation claims, provider data, and utilization stats.

- **[GTFS (General Transit Feed Specification)](https://gtfs.org/)** — Standard format for US public transit data. Most major US cities publish free GTFS feeds. Use it to combine transit with NEMT routing.

- **[Medicaid NEMT Policy Guide (CMS)](https://www.medicaid.gov/medicaid/benefits/transportation/index.html)** — Official CMS documentation on NEMT as a Medicaid benefit. Required reading for anyone building in this space.

### Communication Tools

- **[Twilio](https://www.twilio.com/)** — Industry-standard SMS, voice, and WhatsApp API. Free tier: 1,000 SMS/month. Use for patient ride notifications and driver dispatch. HIPAA-eligible.
  > *The standard for building NEMT patient communication workflows in the US.*

- **[Vonage (formerly Nexmo)](https://www.vonage.com/communications-apis/)** — Alternative to Twilio. SMS, voice, and video APIs. HIPAA Business Associate Agreement available.

