## 🧠 Mental Health AI

> AI tools for mental health screening, support, and crisis detection in US clinical settings.

*Mental health is one of the largest unmet needs in US healthcare. 1 in 5 Americans experience mental illness. Only 46% get treatment.*

- **[Woebot Health (Research)](https://woebothealth.com/)** — Clinically studied AI chatbot delivering Cognitive Behavioral Therapy (CBT). RCT-validated. Being used in US healthcare systems.
  > *CBT is first-line treatment for depression and anxiety. Woebot delivers it at scale.*

- **[Wysa](https://www.wysa.com/)** — AI mental health chatbot. Free for individuals. API available for integration into US health platforms. FDA Breakthrough Device designation.

- **[Crisis Text Line (Open Data)](https://www.crisistextline.org/data-philosophy/)** — Shares anonymized research data from 250M+ crisis text messages. Use it to train crisis detection models. Free for researchers.

- **[PHQ-9 & GAD-7 Screening Tools (SAMHSA)](https://www.integration.samhsa.gov/clinical-practice/screening-tools)** — Free, validated depression and anxiety screening instruments used across the US. Build them into your intake workflows.

- **[NIMH Mental Health Research Data](https://nda.nih.gov/)** — National Institute of Mental Health data sharing platform. Free access to mental health research datasets for qualified researchers.

- **[Mental Health America Screening Tools](https://screening.mhanational.org/screening-tools/)** — Free online screening tools for depression, anxiety, PTSD, and more. API integration possible.

