## 🔒 HIPAA, Privacy & Responsible AI

> Building health AI in the US requires HIPAA compliance. These tools and frameworks help.

*HIPAA is not optional. Any app handling Protected Health Information (PHI) must comply.*

### HIPAA Compliance Tools

- **[AWS HIPAA Eligible Services](https://aws.amazon.com/compliance/hipaa-eligible-services-reference/)** — Free reference list of AWS services covered under their Business Associate Agreement (BAA). Build HIPAA-compliant infrastructure on AWS.

- **[Google Cloud HIPAA Compliance](https://cloud.google.com/security/compliance/hipaa)** — Google Cloud's HIPAA compliance guide. BAA available for covered services.

- **[Medplum](https://www.medplum.com/)** — (See EHR section.) Open-source FHIR platform with HIPAA and SOC2 compliance built in.

### AI Fairness & Bias Tools

- **[AI Fairness 360 (IBM)](https://aif360.mybluemix.net/)** — Free, open-source toolkit to detect and fix bias in AI models. Python library + interactive demos.
  > *Most health AI is trained on non-representative data. This checks if your model treats everyone fairly.*

- **[Google What-If Tool](https://pair-code.github.io/what-if-tool/)** — Free browser-based tool to explore how your model makes decisions across different patient groups. No code needed.

- **[NIST AI Risk Management Framework](https://www.nist.gov/publications/artificial-intelligence-risk-management-framework-ai-rmf-10)** — Free PDF. The US government's official guide to building trustworthy AI. Increasingly referenced in grant applications, regulatory submissions, and NIW petitions.

### Privacy-Preserving AI

- **[PySyft](https://github.com/OpenMined/PySyft)** — Free Python library for federated learning and differential privacy. Train AI on patient data across multiple hospitals without centralizing PHI.

- **[TensorFlow Federated](https://www.tensorflow.org/federated)** — Google's open-source federated learning framework. Train shared models across hospitals without sharing patient data.

- **[OpenDP](https://opendp.org/)** — Free library for differential privacy. Share aggregate health statistics without exposing individual patient data.

