## 📖 Research & US Policy Reports

> Key papers and US government reports — with plain-English summaries.

### Key Research Papers

- **[Deep Learning for Medical Image Analysis (Litjens et al., 2017)](https://arxiv.org/abs/1702.05747)** — Comprehensive survey of deep learning in medical imaging. 9,000+ citations.
  > *Plain English: The foundational paper on AI in radiology and pathology. Read this before building any medical imaging AI.*

- **[Racial Bias in Dermatology AI (Daneshjou et al., 2021)](https://www.nature.com/articles/s41591-020-01192-7)** — Proves that skin disease AI trained on non-diverse data fails on dark skin tones.
  > *Plain English: If your training data is mostly white patients, your model won't work for everyone. This paper is the evidence.*

- **[AI-First Medicaid: How CMS Can Build a Smarter Safety Net (2025)](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC12663265/)** — Policy roadmap for deploying AI within US Medicaid programs.
  > *Plain English: How AI can reduce the $360B/year US healthcare administrative waste and improve care for 90M Medicaid beneficiaries.*

- **[ClinicalBERT: Modeling Clinical Notes (Alsentzer et al., 2019)](https://arxiv.org/abs/1904.05342)** — How to use BERT language models on clinical notes from EHRs.

### US Government Reports & Frameworks

- **[NIST AI Risk Management Framework (2023)](https://www.nist.gov/publications/artificial-intelligence-risk-management-framework-ai-rmf-10)** — Free PDF. The US standard for trustworthy AI. Referenced in FDA guidance, ONC rules, and NIW petitions.

- **[ONC Federal Health IT Strategic Plan 2024–2030](https://www.healthit.gov/topic/onc-strategic-plan)** — The US Office of the National Coordinator's roadmap for health IT. Understand where US policy is heading.

- **[CMS Digital Health Ecosystem Framework (2025)](https://www.cms.gov/)** — CMS's vision for AI and digital health in Medicaid and Medicare. Includes FHIR API mandates.

- **[FDA AI/ML-Based Software as a Medical Device (SaMD) Action Plan](https://www.fda.gov/medical-devices/software-medical-device-samd/artificial-intelligence-and-machine-learning-aiml-enabled-medical-devices)** — Free. Required reading if your AI tool assists in diagnosis or treatment. Covers FDA oversight of health AI.

- **[21st Century Cures Act (ONC)](https://www.healthit.gov/curesrule/)** — US law that mandated FHIR APIs for health data exchange. Understand what US health systems are legally required to do.

