## 🤝 US Communities & Organizations

> The organizations and communities driving health AI in the US.

- **[HIMSS (Healthcare Information and Management Systems Society)](https://www.himss.org/)** — The largest US health IT professional organization. Annual conference, free resources, and policy reports.

- **[HL7 International](https://www.hl7.org/)** — The organization that maintains FHIR. Free access to FHIR specifications and working groups.

- **[ONC (Office of the National Coordinator for Health IT)](https://www.healthit.gov/)** — US government office responsible for health IT policy. Free datasets, toolkits, and standards.

- **[AHRQ (Agency for Healthcare Research and Quality)](https://www.ahrq.gov/)** — US federal agency funding health services research. Free datasets, tools, and grant opportunities.

- **[Partnership on AI](https://partnershiponai.org/)** — Coalition including Microsoft, Google, Apple, and Amazon working on responsible AI in healthcare and other sectors. Free resources.

- **[AI Now Institute](https://ainowinstitute.org/)** — Research on social and policy implications of AI, including health equity. Free reports.

- **[NCVHS (National Committee on Vital and Health Statistics)](https://ncvhs.hhs.gov/)** — Federal advisory committee on health data policy. Free transcripts and reports.

- **[National Academy of Medicine](https://nam.edu/programs/value-science-driven-health-care/artificial-intelligence-in-health-and-health-care/)** — Free reports on AI in healthcare from the US scientific advisory body.

