## 💡 Project Ideas

> Real problems in US healthcare that need builders. Pick one.

### Beginner Friendly

- [ ] **Medicaid NEMT route optimizer** — Use Vroom + OpenRouteService to optimally assign dialysis patients to drivers. Input: patient addresses + dialysis center. Output: optimal routes. Saves Medicaid money.

- [ ] **FHIR patient data viewer** — Build a simple web app using Blue Button 2.0 to let Medicare patients view their own claims data in plain English instead of medical codes.

- [ ] **Community health needs dashboard** — Pull County Health Rankings data + US Census data and visualize health disparities by county. Identify where FQHCs should expand.

- [ ] **PHQ-9 / GAD-7 intake form** — Build a HIPAA-compliant digital mental health screening intake that feeds results into an OpenEMR or Medplum instance via FHIR.

### Intermediate

- [ ] **Clinical note summarizer** — Use MedSpaCy or ClinicalBERT to extract key information (diagnoses, medications, allergies) from discharge notes and generate a patient-friendly summary.

- [ ] **Medication adherence SMS bot** — Use Twilio + RapidPro to send automated, personalized medication reminders to Medicaid patients. Track responses to identify non-adherence.

- [ ] **NEMT broker comparison tool** — Scrape CMS NEMT claims data to compare broker performance (on-time rate, cost per trip) by state and county.

- [ ] **Health equity gap finder** — Combine MIMIC-IV data with demographic information to identify which patient groups receive worse care outcomes. Use AI Fairness 360 to quantify bias.

### Advanced

- [ ] **Federated EHR learning network** — Use PySyft to train a shared readmission prediction model across 3+ OpenEMR instances without sharing patient data.

- [ ] **Prior authorization AI assistant** — Use NLP to read a patient's clinical notes and automatically draft a prior authorization letter for insurance, with relevant clinical evidence cited.

- [ ] **AI-powered FQHC scheduling optimizer** — Predict no-show rates by patient using historical EHR data, then optimize appointment scheduling to reduce gaps in federally qualified health centers.

